nt opportunities\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 323}, {\"ngram\": \"economic benefit\", \"from\": 325, \"to\": 341}, {\"ngram\": \"pride\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 351}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 355, \"to\": 361}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A coalition of labor unions wants to ensure that roughly 36,000 L.A. tourism workers see some of that prosperity in the form of an \\\"Olympic wage.\\\"\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 532, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A coalition\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 397}, {\"ngram\": \"labor unions\", \"from\": 401, \"to\": 413}, {\"ngram\": \"roughly 36,000 L.A. tourism workers\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 470}, {\"ngram\": \"that prosperity\", \"from\": 483, \"to\": 498}, {\"ngram\": \"the form\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 510}, {\"ngram\": \"an \\\"Olympic wage\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 530}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At a rally outside L.A. City Hall on Tuesday, accompanied by some City Council members, a coalition representing workers at LAX, hotels and other tourism sectors renewed calls for animmediate boost in workers' minimum wageto $25 an hour, with incremental increases to $30 an hour by 2028.\", \"from\": 534, \"to\": 822, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 600, \"end\": 612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_Council\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 2.0201242067778372e-12, \"text\": \"City Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_Council\"}, {\"begin\": 658, \"end\": 661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_International_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.070827463589143e-15, \"text\": \"LAX\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_International_Airport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a rally\", \"from\": 537,